      "citation_id": "[CITATION_4]",
      "span_text": "Yet, the recent finding that both WWP1  , an E3 ligase capable of forming K11-, K48-and K63-polyubiquitin chains, and ATXN3, a DUB that prefers K63-chain substrate, function in HTT ubiquitylation, suggests there may be formation of heterotypic polyubiquitin chains  that will complicates the degradation of HTT by UPS."
    },
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_5]",
      "span_text": "Yet, the recent finding that both WWP1  , an E3 ligase capable of forming K11-, K48-and K63-polyubiquitin chains, and ATXN3, a DUB that prefers K63-chain substrate, function in HTT ubiquitylation, suggests there may be formation of heterotypic polyubiquitin chains  that will complicates the degradation of HTT by UPS."
